f=Engineering/raj/custom/service-patterns/assets/stack-notes-node-backend-2026-07.md · h1:Stack Notes Node.js Backend Patterns (dated 2026-07)=**Applies business's stack-profile names Node.js (Express Next.js API routes).** Method authority: `service-patterns` `api-standards` (conflicts resolve there). Source: affaan-m/everything-claude-code `backend-patterns`, adopted 2026-07-10, condensed. Rail unchanged: destructive data access backend, ever. · h2:Layering=**Repository pattern:** data access behind interface (`findAll/findById/create/update/delete`) swap stores without touching business logic; store itself comes dana stack-profile., **Service layer:** business logic composed over repositories; SQL/store calls route handlers., **Middleware pipeline:** auth (`withAuth` wrapper verifying bearer token `req.user`), logging, rate limiting composable wrappers, inline handlers. · h2:Data access (raj's data-access-discipline governs)=Select needed columns, never `select('*')`., N+1: batch-fetch collected IDs Map one query, one row., Multi-write consistency: real transactions (DB function/RPC) never sequential writes hoping best. Transaction *scripts* mutate schema/data dana-authored (Rail 3). · h2:Caching=Cache-aside TTL (check cache miss fetch `setex`) explicit invalidation write decorator repository (`CachedMarketRepository` wrapping base repo) keeps caching out business logic. · h2:Errors=Typed `ApiError(statusCode, message)` one centralized handler mapping: ApiError status validation error 400 details unknown log generic 500 (never leak internals). Retry exponential backoff (1s/2s/4s, capped attempts) transient upstream failures. · h2:AuthN/AuthZ (api-standards owns contract; aegis reviews surface)=JWT verification helper throwing 401 missing/invalid role→permission map `requirePermission(...)` HOF wrapping handlers (403 insufficient). · h2:Rate limiting (critical note)=**Shared store only** (Redis gateway platform limiter). Per-process in-memory counters fail production: reset deploy, split across replicas, fail open serverless. · h2:Background work=Slow work goes queue; endpoint returns "queued" immediately. In-memory queue single-instance dev production queues stack-profile (e.g. BullMQ, SQS). · h2:Logging=Structured JSON `requestId`/`userId` context, error+stack captured feeds `backend-observability` (its rules secrets/PII apply).